HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1041
By Todd
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Dr. Hyran E. Barefoot
on the celebration of his ninety-eighth birthday.
WHEREAS, it is the privilege of the members of this General Assembly to honor those
exemplary citizens who have dedicated their lives to the cultivation of wisdom, the service of
their communities, and the education of future generations; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Hyran E. Barefoot, the fourteenth president of Union University and a
respected scholar, is celebrating the momentous occasion of his ninety-eighth birthday, marking
nearly a century of faithful service, leadership, and influence; and
WHEREAS, a native of Mantee, Mississippi, Dr. Barefoot first arrived in Jackson in 1957
to join the Union University faculty, eventually adopting Jackson as his true home and the place
where he and his late wife, Joyce, would raise their three daughters—Judy, June, and Jane;
and
WHEREAS, Dr. Barefoot's tenure at Union University is a testament to his versatility and
dedication, having served with distinction as a professor of religion and Greek, an academic
dean, the university president from 1987 to 1996, and subsequently as chancellor; and
WHEREAS, known affectionately as the "Teacher President," Dr. Barefoot maintained
his love for the classroom even while leading the university, continuing to teach students and
famously remarking that his favorite courses were those with the "least amount of grading"; and
WHEREAS, under Dr. Barefoot's presidential leadership, Union University experienced a
remarkable era of stability and growth, including record enrollments that doubled the student
body, the expansion of the Penick Academic Complex, and the construction of the Hyran E.
Barefoot Student Union Building, which stands as a physical testament to Dr. Barefoot's impact;
and
